    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-11T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="489"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.91293/7–1149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-11T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 11, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 11—7:57 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 709. Re Generalissimo’s press interview from Formosa, reliably informed by
                    other American correspondents who also sought interview unsuccessfully that
                    apparently special considerations resulted <pb facs="0431" n="421"
                        xml:id="pg_421"/> choice INS<note n="82" xml:id="d489fn82">International
                        News Service.</note> Handelman and Scripps-Howard Farnsworth. Handelman came
                    specially from Tokyo to attend. Others had been turned down only few days before
                    grounds Generalissimo in retirement. Seems possible suggestion originated
                    Stateside, possibly Madame,<note n="83" xml:id="d489fn83">Madame Chiang
                        Kai-shek.</note> for interview with attention paid propaganda value there in
                    China aid cause.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
